comments.content: SoundHound.
Handy level, flashlight, New York Times. The first two are free. You're gonna love the freaking thing, S.

SoundPrism is also a fun music tool. SoundHound is that app that lets you hum a song into it, and it'll tell you what song it is. If you've ever got something stuck in your head, or if you hear a song on a commercial or in a restaurant, you can look it up like that. I use it a lot.

Twitter and Facebook have lovely apps. iHeartradio or Pandora or some other radio app. Ascension is an amazing board/card game that has an amazing app version. Shazam for song recognition. Fandango has a fine app if you're into that sort of thing.
Buy Animoog now while it is still $.99!!!  Also, Camera+, ProHDR, Comiczeal, Skype, Dropbox...
Weatherbug,  AP Mobile, amazon, garage band, flashlight, night sky, Netflix, adobe ideas - you'll love it.
Pandora, BBC News, Dragon Dictation, PhotoGene, Instagram, TiltShift, CardStar, iQueue lite (to manage your netflix queue). For games, I like Ragdoll Blaster.
You could also look at: aroundme, find iphone, blitz, sudoku, cut the rope, icon project (makes shortcuts)
Angry birds.  :-) . Popblock.
Unblock me. Penguin app - you can watch them all day. Yelp
Yelp for sure too!

Congrats!  Some great apps suggested here.  I second Dropbox, Instagram, any Flashlight that uses your camera flash, and Find iPhone.  Other must haves:  FirstClass, ESPN Scorecenter, MapQuest (turn-by-turn voice GPS navigation).  Also would enjoy:  Starbucks, Yelp, EZ Receipts for WageWorks FSA submissions, RedLaser, KeyRing, BeerCloud, Foursquare, and Vtok (videochat with more flexibility than Facetime).
My dad says "Droid".
Forgot Photoshop Express - a must have as well...
Also Radio Paradise.
Spotify, flipboard, keyring, pano, imdb,
iMovie
I'll add: USA Today, ToDo and Kindle apps.  You're gonna love your iPhone!
I thought you lived in Ohio ; )
You will totally become addicted. I suggest pandora. Any mobile banking from your bank is helpful. Also urbanspoon. Welcome to the modern age
Now you can text with your cheap friend (me) using the IPhone to IPhone app (after you teach me how to download it)
Awesome, people.  Thanks.  Still getting used to the thing, like driving a new expensive car.  (I assume.)  Still accepting suggestions, of course.
One other thing it helped my husband get use to his phone was to leave the sounds on for typing etc until he was really comfortable then turned it all off to save battery life.
